race.comment: SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET (7) and NDOLA (3) come through a good BM84 at Caulfield last time out. SUNSHINEINMYPOCKET started $2.60 there and just got held up a touch as NDOLA went for home. Doubt there's much between them but the former can certainly turn the tables, possible better set up with the wide draw. NDOLA is flying and looks a strong danger again. PERSIAN SPIRIT (12) has come back very well. He was unsuited staying at 1200m last time, now up in trip he can improve although he'll need a touch of luck early. HE'LL RIP (14) is racing well and did win impressively over this route two back, he can land just off the pace here and run a competitive race.
